thread.title: University of Northern Colorado fall just short of historic upset
thread.title_full: University of Northern Colorado fall just short of historic upset

author: samuel mustari
title: University of Northern Colorado fall just short of historic upset
text: Smaller Larger Related Media The University of Northern Colorado football team recovered an onside kick and scored in the final minutes of the game to take a one-point lead on No. 7 Eastern Washington, but a last-second field goal doomed the upset bid. Jordan Descalo kicked a 44-yard field goal as time ran out to give Eastern Washington the win. UNC falls to 2-3 in the Big Sky and 4-3 overall. Eastern Washington improves to 3-0 in conference and 5-2 overall. Check back to www.greeeleytribune.com later today.
